			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes, Gimblax can be pretty easy. The group stays at ZI, and you run all the way to the end of the dungeon where Gimblax is standing there by himself. You have to be careful though. There will be a few mobs enroute that see invis, and you'll either have to time your movement past them in between ticks or just run and fade them off at the end.
<br />

<br />
Pull Gimblax and run him to ZI, aiming for either the left or right wall and fade him there. He'll just stand there while all the other mobs walk back. If you fade too early (before he gets outside of the castle), he'll walk back and you'll have to do it all over.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes things can just go wrong though. I've personally gotten stunned by a see invis mob on the way back and gotten killed, and been rooted (that I couldn't believe) and got killed. This of course can cause problems... you won't have enough mana for the fades to try again until you regen it, and you have to get your corpse back (may not be a problem depending on the classes you have present). If it's gotten to that point, it may just be easier to fight to Gimblax. This generally will only take 20-25 minutes itself if you only fight when you have to, ie when you have to cross paths with a see invis mob.
<br />

<br />
The lockout timer for all single group missions is 25 minutes from when you requested it, so even if you complete it in 10 minutes and it takes you 5 minutes to get there, you have to wait 10 minutes to request it again.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
