			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: DON Spoiler<a name="75366"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 12 05 2:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Front Page is your friend!  Muahahaha
<br />

<br />
In DoN, there is 2 factions, the good and the evil. This is a walkthro on the good side of the quest (i would assume the evil side is similar). 
<br />

<br />
A note that will help during the quest. First, download the maps. They can be found at http://www.mapfiend.net/ . The missions are similar to ldons. In Lavastorm, go to where I have marked 1 with a group. The group leader hails the mission givers and can pick a task to do. When the grp leader selects a task, the box pops up for the grp telling the grp the task and the award (a token for faction and a number of crystals. After you have a task, zone into Broodlands and look at your compass, it like ldon will mark the ZI to your instance. Once you zone in, follow the tasks that is on the box. You can pull up the task box at any time by typing Alt Q. When you finish the tasks, you will be awarded the token and the numbers of crystals. Take this token BEFORE you do another task to the merchents in lavastorm. I have them marked on the map with a 2. 
<br />

<br />
As you get more wins, (and faction goes up), more tasks open up for you to be able to do, and be able to progress further in this quest. 
<br />
 
<br />

<br />
Task Group 1 
<br />

<br />
To be able to start task group 1, need to be indifferent to the good camp, or 5 faction turn ins from the tokens by doing the missons. When you have 5 wins or you are indifferent to the good camp, talk to Chieftain Relae Aderi. Hail and say &quot;i will help&quot;. Next talk to Private Nylean Kel`Ther. On hail, you will get 3 tasks. 
<br />

<br />
1. Create an Antidote. Loot 5 Boiling Lavaspinner Blood. The lavaspinners that you need are found in the zone Lavaspinner's Lair. They are located where I have marked 1. Drop rate pretty common, about 1 in 2 drop the blood. They are green to light blue, very easy solo kill. 
<br />
 
<br />

<br />
2. Greed of the Goblins. Kill 11 Stillmoon laborers. These are found in Stillmoon Temple. These are light blue to blue, pretty easy solos, think max hit around 250. They are found randomly in the zone, most common near the zone in 
<br />

<br />
3. Burning Arrows. Loot 5 Delvian Goblin Tooth. These goblins are found in Tirranum's Delve. Tirranum's Delve is in Lavaspinners Lair and is marked on the map. Any Delve in Tirranum's Delve can drop the tooth and is a very common drop. The delves are light blue and blue, and a fairly easy solo. 
<br />

<br />
These 3 can be done in any order. When all 3 are done, go back to Chieftain Relae Aderi and hail him, then hail Keeper Dilar Nelune. Keeper Dilar Nelune will give you a task called Children of Gimblax. Take this task with a group and do the misson. Consists of killing a named called Gimblax. He is a red con and at the far south side of the zone. Can invis passed most the zone (note that the evokers see invis), and tho he is a red con, very easy kill. 
<br />
 
<br />

<br />
Reward: Once Gimblax is dead, hail Chieftain Relae Aderi. You will get a flag, 3 AAs and the AA Gift of the Keepers. Gives you +10 to all stats, and +10 to all the stat caps. 
<br />

<br />
Task Group 2 
<br />

<br />
To be able to start task group 2, need to be amiable to the good camp, or 10 faction turn ins from the tokens by doing the missons. When you have 10 wins or you are amiable to the good camp, talk to Chieftain Relae Aderi. Hail and say &quot;what work&quot;. Next talk to Private Nylean Kel`Ther. On hail, you will get 3 tasks. 
<br />

<br />
1. Defend the Kirin Contact. Kill 9 Kirins in the zone The Ascent. The zone The Ascent is found in Stillmoon Temple, and marked on the map. The highest concentration of Kilin's can be found on the 2nd level of the zone. 
<br />

<br />
2. Recover the Lost Map. Loot 8 Shredded Map Piece. These drop off the pumas and leapords in The Ascent. 
<br />

<br />
3. Turn the Tides of the Sand. Loot 7 Sandy Goblin Blood. These drops are in the Stillmoon Temple, off the Stillmoon's. 
<br />

<br />
These 3 can be done in any order. When all 3 are done, go back to Chieftain Relae Aderi and hail him, then hail Keeper Dilar Nelune. Keeper Dilar Nelune will give you a task called Sickness of the Spirit. 
<br />

<br />
Sickness of the Spirit is an instanced mission, ZI in Broodlands. 
<br />
 
<br />
1. Kill the Stillmoon Courtyard Gardener, and loot a Perfect Chery Blossum. 
<br />
2. Give the Perfect Chery Blossum to the Stillmoon Forest Keeper, marked by a 1 on the map. 
<br />
3. Go to Wong Li, marked by a 2 on the map and hail. 
<br />
4. Go to the bath marked by a 3 on the map. 
<br />
5. A named called Nethran will pop to the south of the bath, kill and loot an Ancient Note. 
<br />
6. Give the Ancient Note to Wong Li. 
<br />
7. Go the the library marked by 4 on the map and hail the a Stillmoon librarian. 
<br />
8. Go to the ZO, marked by 5 on the map. Here, need to kill a scroll thief and 3 scroll thief underlings. Loot the Fables of Winged Harmony. 
<br />
9. Go back to Wong Li, give him the Fables of Winged Harmony. Wong Li will repop, now kill Wong Li. 
<br />

<br />
Talking to Chieftain Relae Aderi he will refer you to talk to Lieutenant Ekiltu Verlor. Lieutenant Ekiltu Verlor will allow you to trigger a 24 person task called Calling Emoush. 
<br />

<br />
Calling Emoush: 
<br />
Take at least 12 people with you and trigger the task. Zone in, and clear / invis to the named area. Emoush the Destroyer is surrounded by 3 adds, Mystic Braggle, Mystic Griknok and Mystic Shiflor. Gather raid away from the named and pull these adds single one at time. They do not die, just FD when hps reach zero. When all 3 adds are FD, pull and dps Emoush. After roughly 2 min, he will DA, and the 3 Mystics will repop. Again pull and get them to FD one at a time. Repeat till Emoush is dead. Emoush will drop 6 Glowing Stone Fragments and a random 125 hp/mana drop. The stone is for the quest. 
<br />

<br />
Reward: When you are at this stage in the quest, turn in the Glowing Stone Fragment to Chieftain Relae Aderi. He will give you your lvl 69 spell, roughly 3AA, and the AA Valor of the Keeper, which increases HP, Mana and Endurance. (not sure on exact #s yet, but think was around 200). 
<br />

<br />
Task Group 3 
<br />

<br />
To be able to start task group 3, I was amiable to the good camp, and keeping with the pattern, assuming need 15 faction turn ins from the tokens by doing the missons (I had more then 15 at this point, as not able to confirm if able to trigger these tasks with only 14 wins). Talk to Chieftain Relae Aderi. Hail and say &quot;what lauded work&quot;, then &quot;what quests&quot;, then what wyvrns. Next talk to Private Nylean Kel`Ther. On hail, you will get 3 tasks. 
<br />

<br />
1. Protect the Waters. Loot 5 Purified Nest Waters in the zone Stillmoon Temple. Fastest way to get the water is clearing the Stillmoon's at the ZI of Stillmoon Temple, common drop at ZI. Does NOT have to be a Stillmoon water servent to drop the water. 
<br />

<br />
2. Snowfoot Revenge. Kill 10 Snowfoot goblins in the zone The Ascent. The Snowfoot are at the end of the 2nd section of the zone, can invis passed most of the zone, watch for see invis tho, there is random see invis. 
<br />

<br />
3. The Sacred Scrolls. Loot 7 Ancient Scroll of Wisdom in the zone Thunderquest Isles. These drop off the 3 kinds of Sentinels: an earthen sentinel, a mud sentinel, and a clay sentinel. Best place I found to kill these I marked in yellow on the map. 
<br />
 
<br />

<br />
These 3 can be done in any order. When all 3 are done, go back to Chieftain Relae Aderi and hail him, then hail Keeper Dilar Nelune. Keeper Dilar Nelune will give you a 1 group task called History of the Isle. 
<br />

<br />
History of the Isle: 
<br />
1. Need a decent tank and 2 healers is nice (clr and dru, or 2 dru). CC is helpful as well, but not needed. Zone into the instance and you will get a task to go to the lower section of the Halls of History. Head to where I have marked 1 on the map. The Pumas see invis. On the bridge near the ZI, there is 4 Pumas. Once these are dead, you can invis all the way to the building that is marked with a 1. In that building, there is random see invis, so can try to scout in and see how far you can get in invis, or just clear from there. 
<br />
  
<br />
2. When you get to the 1 marked on the map, will trigger 3 more tasks, all being to kill the sentry guarding one of the artifacts of Yar`Lir. 
<br />
3. As you continue to explore the building marked with a 1, you will find a red con named Protector of the Halls. Quads for 1535, has a rampage, partial slowable. Kill. On death, get a task complete, and a new task, to Recover the (name of the artifact). There is 3 Protector of the Halls, and 3 artifacts to loot - Gift of Yar`Lir, Strength of Yar`Lir and the Fury of Lar`Lir. On the last named kill, you will get the artifact plus a box called Holding of Yar`Lir. 
<br />
4. The 3 artifacts and the box are dropable, but the person that needs this flag needs to do the combine. On combine, get the Secret of Yar`Lir 
<br />

<br />
Talking to Lieutenant Ekiltu Verlor he will have 2 new events for you. First is the Trial of Perseverance, a 24 max person event, and Volkara's Bite, a 42 max person event. 
<br />

<br />
Trial of Perserverance: 
<br />
This is a 24 person raid, is triggered by talking to Lieutenant Ekiltu Verlor. When you zone in, there will only be one mob up, a drake named Osashi. When you are ready, tell Osashi 'Ready'. This is trigger 4 Stillmoon goblins. They spawn around the bell near ZI. Kill the 4 goblins, after a few minutes, the Stillmoon warlord will spawn. Kill. The warlord will drop 6 Goblin Warlord's Beads that is needed for the quest. 
<br />

<br />
Volkara's Bite: 
<br />
This is a 42 person raid. If you have done the hivequeen raid in WoS, it is very similar event. You need to kill a spider named Volkara. As you damage Volkara, Egg Sacks spawn. These need to be killed asap. All dps off named when they spawn. If you do not kill the Egg Sacks fast enough, Magma Spiderling spawn. Do not damage Volkara whenever an Egg Sack or a Magma Spiderling is up. On Volkara's death, about 25-30 Magma Spiderlings spawn. Kite and assist heals as needed to get these dead. Another way (and easier) way to get rid of these 25-30 adds when Volkara is dead is to have an evacer in each group and evac the moment Volkara is dead, they will despawn. Volkara drops 9 Lava Spider Spinners that are needed for the quest. 
<br />
 
<br />

<br />
Reward: When you have the drops from History of the Isle, Trial of Perserverance and Volara's Bite, give these drops to Chieftain Relae Aderi. You will recieve 2 AAs, and the AA Embrace of the Keepers. This will give you 5 more buff slots. 
<br />

<br />
Task Group 4 
<br />

<br />
Talking to Chieftain Relae Aderi he will tell you to talk to Lieutenant Ekiltu Verlor. He will now give you to more events to do, a 24 person event Goblin Dojo and a 42 event Guardian of the Sands. 
<br />

<br />
Goblin Dojo: 
<br />
This is a 24 person event. Needed for this is decent heals, and 5 tanks, and a mezer. On port in, do not go in the room till the raid is ready, as the trigger for the raid is walking in the room. This event is killing waves of mobs. During the waves, you will get AEed, the dot can be cured with RC. 
<br />
Wave 1 = 5 mobs, Disciple of Water, Disciple of Earth, Disciple of Wood, Disciple of Fire and the Disciple of Metal. Is best to have the tanks have a pre target before they charge the raid. At least one will be mezable, use the mezed Disciple as a hold mob to give time to med and rez if needed. 
<br />
Wave 2 = 4 mobs and starts 2 minute after the last Disciple is dead. Master of Doubt, Master of Deciet, Master of Rage and the Master of Contentment. Again, get pre targets before they charge, and find the mezable to use as the hold mob. 
<br />
Wave 3 = 3 mobs and starts 3 minutes after the last Master is dead. Grandmaster Puma, Grandmaster Beetle and the Grandmaster Snake. Again, get pre targets before they charge, and find the mezable to use as the hold mob. 
<br />
Wave 4 = 2 mobs and starts 4 minutes after the last Grandmaster is dead. Steel and Silk are the names, and neither are mezable. 
<br />
Wave 5 = Storm Reach Sensei. He casts as AE FD and stun. Kill. He will drop 6 Meditation Stone's that is needed for the quest.&#160;
<br />
  </span></td>
